The rhododendron blooms speckled the entire trail to High Shoals Falls. It was a bright summer day, but the rhododendron thrived in the darker, wetter regions on the mountain. They smelled wonderful! The Lady Bird Johnson Wildflower center mentions that the rhododendron's nickname is the Great laurel and craftsmen sometimes use its wood to make tool handles. These fragrant, fluffy flowers were quite a sight.
